<TITLE> Hill women enforce transport blockade in Rangamati </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, June 12 (bdnews24.com)  Road and water ways were blocked in the hill district on Saturday by The Hill Women's Federation (HWF), a front organisation of the United People's Democratic Front (UPDF). HWF enforced the blockade in observance of 'Kalpana Chakma Kidnapping Day' at the district headquarter, HWF sources said. The hill women are also demanding publication of the investigation report on Kalpana's kidnapping way back in 1996. The blockade programme got under way at 6am and would continue till 2pm, they said. Hill Women's Federation leader Kalpana Chakma was kidnapped on June 12, 1996. From then on, the organisation has been observing June 12 of every year as Kalpana Chakma Kidnapping Day. HWF general secretary Kanika Chakma told bdnews24.com that the blockade programme was taken up after the district administration refused to allow the organization to hold a women's gathering at the local municipality auditorium in observance of the day. bdnews24.
